# BookForge Runtime Specification
# Agentic Technical Book Synthesis from Knowledge Graphs

id: bookforge-runtime
title: BookForge Runtime - Agentic Technical Book Synthesis
version: 1.0.0
status: implemented
purpose: >
  Transform structured knowledge graphs into professionally written technical books
  through a deterministic pipeline of research, planning, synthesis, and publishing.
  BookForge treats writing as the final stage of a much larger research, planning,
  and synthesis pipeline, ensuring technical accuracy, internal consistency, and
  evidence-backed publications.

requirements:
  - System must import and analyze knowledge graphs from SovereignSpec projects
  - System must perform semantic survey to discover concepts and relationships
  - System must organize concepts into coherent themes and structures
  - System must identify knowledge gaps and perform additional research
  - System must construct evidence-backed outlines and chapter specifications
  - System must generate technical illustration specifications
  - System must produce internally consistent manuscripts
  - System must review content using multiple specialized agents
  - System must compile publications into PDF, EPUB, and HTML formats
  - System must track provenance for all generated content
  - System must support continuous publishing when knowledge base changes
  - System must preserve all intermediate artifacts for reproducibility

constraints:
  - No direct LLM-to-book generation without pipeline stages
  - All intermediate artifacts must be persisted to disk
  - Every paragraph must be traceable to source evidence
  - Pipeline stages must be independently reproducible
  - Knowledge graph serves as single source of truth
  - No external API calls required for core functionality
  - Local-first architecture using Ollama for inference
  - Must support incremental updates when knowledge graph changes

acceptance_criteria:
  - Given a valid knowledge graph, system produces complete book blueprint
  - Given chapter specifications, system generates evidence-backed chapters
  - Given generated chapters, system produces technical review reports
  - Given reviewed content, system compiles to PDF/EPUB/HTML formats
  - Given knowledge graph updates, system identifies affected chapters
  - Given affected chapters, system regenerates only impacted sections
  - Given any pipeline stage, system produces inspectable artifacts
  - Given concept discovery, system identifies relationships and dependencies
  - Given theme construction, system groups concepts into coherent structures
  - Given evidence collection, system links every paragraph to sources

api_specification:
  endpoints:
    - path: /api/graph/import
      method: POST
      request:
        body:
          graph_path: string (required)
          format: string (required)
      response:
        200:
          graph_id: string
          node_count: integer
          edge_count: integer
        400:
          error: string

    - path: /api/survey/{graph_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          graph_id: string (required)
      response:
        200:
          survey_id: string
          concepts: array
          relationships: array
          gaps: array
        404:
          error: string

    - path: /api/themes/{survey_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          survey_id: string (required)
      response:
        200:
          theme_id: string
          themes: array
          concept_groups: array

    - path: /api/blueprint/{theme_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          theme_id: string (required)
          title: string (optional)
      response:
        200:
          blueprint_id: string
          parts: array
          chapters: array
          learning_objectives: array

    - path: /api/chapters/{blueprint_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          blueprint_id: string (required)
          chapter_id: string (optional)
      response:
        200:
          chapter_specs: array
          evidence_maps: array
          illustration_specs: array

    - path: /api/generate/{chapter_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          chapter_id: string (required)
      response:
        200:
          draft_id: string
          content: string
          citations: array
          word_count: integer

    - path: /api/review/{draft_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          draft_id: string (required)
          review_type: string (required)
      response:
        200:
          review_id: string
          issues: array
          recommendations: array
          score: float

    - path: /api/compile/{book_id}
      method: POST
      request:
        params:
          book_id: string (required)
          formats: array (required)
      response:
        200:
          compilation_id: string
          outputs: array
          file_paths: array

data_models:
  - name: KnowledgeGraph
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique graph identifier
      - name: nodes
        type: array
        description: Graph nodes containing concepts and entities
      - name: edges
        type: array
        description: Relationships between nodes
      - name: metadata
        type: object
        description: Graph metadata and provenance

  - name: Concept
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique concept identifier
      - name: label
        type: string
        description: Human-readable concept name
      - name: description
        type: string
        description: Concept definition and context
      - name: frequency
        type: integer
        description: Occurrence count in knowledge graph
      - name: relationships
        type: array
        description: Connected concepts and relationship types

  - name: Theme
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique theme identifier
      - name: name
        type: string
        description: Theme title
      - name: concepts
        type: array
        description: Concepts grouped under this theme
      - name: dependencies
        type: array
        description: Prerequisite themes

  - name: BookBlueprint
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique blueprint identifier
      - name: title
        type: string
        description: Book title
      - name: parts
        type: array
        description: High-level book divisions
      - name: chapters
        type: array
        description: Detailed chapter specifications
      - name: learning_objectives
        type: array
        description: What readers will learn

  - name: ChapterSpecification
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique chapter identifier
      - name: title
        type: string
        description: Chapter title
      - name: objectives
        type: array
        description: Chapter learning objectives
      - name: evidence_sources
        type: array
        description: Required evidence and citations
      - name: illustration_specs
        type: array
        description: Technical figures and diagrams
      - name: word_count_target
        type: integer
        description: Target word count

  - name: EvidenceMap
    fields:
      - name: paragraph_id
        type: string
        description: Generated paragraph identifier
      - name: sources
        type: array
        description: Supporting evidence sources
      - name: confidence
        type: float
        description: Evidence strength score
      - name: provenance
        type: object
        description: Source tracking information

  - name: ReviewReport
    fields:
      - name: id
        type: string
        description: Unique review identifier
      - name: chapter_id
        type: string
        description: Chapter being reviewed
      - name: review_type
        type: string
        description: Type of review (technical/editorial/citation)
      - name: issues
        type: array
        description: Identified problems
      - name: recommendations
        type: array
        description: Suggested improvements
      - name: score
        type: float
        description: Quality score (0-1)

test_cases:
  - id: import_sovereignspec_graph
    name: import_sovereignspec_graph
    description: Import SovereignSpec project knowledge graph
    given: SovereignSpec project with knowledge graph
    when: POST /api/graph/import
    then: 200 with graph_id and node/edge counts

  - id: survey_discovers_concepts
    name: survey_discovers_concepts
    description: Survey discovers concepts in knowledge graph
    given: Imported knowledge graph
    when: POST /api/survey/{graph_id}
    then: 200 with concepts, relationships, and gaps

  - id: theme_construction_groups_concepts
    name: theme_construction_groups_concepts
    description: Theme construction groups concepts into coherent themes
    given: Survey results with concepts
    when: POST /api/themes/{survey_id}
    then: 200 with coherent theme groups

  - id: blueprint_generation
    name: blueprint_generation
    description: Generate book blueprint from themes
    given: Theme structure
    when: POST /api/blueprint/{theme_id}
    then: 200 with parts, chapters, and objectives

  - id: chapter_specification_generation
    name: chapter_specification_generation
    description: Generate chapter specifications from blueprint
    given: Book blueprint
    when: POST /api/chapters/{blueprint_id}
    then: 200 with chapter specs and evidence maps

  - id: evidence_backed_generation
    name: evidence_backed_generation
    description: Generate chapter with evidence backing
    given: Chapter specification with evidence
    when: POST /api/generate/{chapter_id}
    then: 200 with citations and provenance

  - id: technical_review_identifies_issues
    name: technical_review_identifies_issues
    description: Technical review identifies issues in chapter
    given: Generated chapter draft
    when: POST /api/review/{draft_id}
    then: 200 with issues and recommendations

  - id: multi_format_compilation
    name: multi_format_compilation
    description: Compile book to multiple formats
    given: Reviewed and finalized book
    when: POST /api/compile/{book_id}
    then: 200 with PDF, EPUB, HTML outputs

  - id: incremental_update_on_graph_change
    name: incremental_update_on_graph_change
    description: Incremental update when knowledge graph changes
    given: Updated knowledge graph
    when: System detects changes
    then: Only affected chapters regenerated

  - id: artifact_preservation
    name: artifact_preservation
    description: Preserve all intermediate artifacts
    given: Any pipeline stage
    when: Stage completes
    then: All intermediate artifacts persisted to disk

references:
  - title: SovereignSpec Documentation
    url: https://github.com/kliewerdaniel/sovereignSpec
  - title: Knowledge Graph Construction Best Practices
    url: https://www.w3.org/TR/knowledge-graph/
  - title: Technical Writing Standards
    url: https://developers.google.com/style

implementation_notes: >
  BookForge implements a deterministic publishing pipeline with five layers:
  Knowledge Layer (graph import and analysis), Research Layer (gap identification
  and evidence collection), Planning Layer (theme construction and blueprint
  generation), Writing Layer (chapter generation with evidence backing), and
  Publishing Layer (multi-format compilation). Each layer produces structured
  artifacts consumed by subsequent stages. The system uses local LLM inference
  via Ollama for all generation tasks, ensuring no data leaves the machine.
  Architecture follows modular agent pattern where specialized agents handle
  specific pipeline stages (Research Analyst, Knowledge Curator, Information
  Architect, Technical Editor, etc.). All intermediate artifacts are persisted
  to enable reproducibility, debugging, and incremental updates when the
  knowledge base evolves.